title: Harbour 

You reach the old harbour.

On the quay, a vendor stands by a rickety tank, filling water into used bottles.  

A delivery drone circles above the water, searching for the best angle for a selfie.  

In the hinterland, a dust storm is brewing, its grit already scratching at your throat.

Between water, dust and drones, you have to decide where to go first.  

- #harbour

@vendor_scene  
title: Go to a water vendor  
tags: harbour
max-visits: 1

You walk over to the tank. Faded posters hang from it, half covered in dust. 

You can still make out the headlines: 
Headline1: Harvests in the region down 70%. 

Headline2: Blackouts hit the outskirts first. 

Headline3: The polycrisis is gaining momentum. 

Vendor: One sip for a coin. Or you keep walking thirsty. 

- #vendor

@pay_vendor  
title: Hand over some crypto
tags: vendor
max-visits: 1

You hand over some crypto. The water tastes metallic, but it eases the scratching in your throat. 

The vendor nods to you, as if waiting to see whether you want to ask anything else.  

- #vendor

@ask_direction 
title: Ask for directions
on-arrival: know-way = 1 
tags: vendor
max-visits: 1

Me: Can you tell me how to get to the teahouse?

Vendor: Follow the water until you reach the long pier with the small lighthouse at the end. 
Down in the old warehouse is the teahouse. You'll recognize it by the paper lanterns. They leave them out even in a storm. 

You thank him, follow his gaze along the water and set off. 

